## AhaDiff

Use AhaDiff to verify and learn from AI-written diffs:

- Run `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` for committed changes.
- Run `ahadiff learn --staged` before committing staged work.
- Run `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` and `ahadiff review` for retention.
- Use `ahadiff verify <run_id>` when checking existing artifacts.
- Use `ahadiff improve <run_id>` for a targeted follow-up.
- Use `ahadiff serve` to inspect local run artifacts.

Generated explanations should be grounded in `claims.jsonl` and file-line
evidence. Treat `.ahadiff/review.sqlite`, `.ahadiff/runs/`, and `prompts/` as
local AhaDiff state unless the repo policy says otherwise. Provider secrets
must stay in environment variables.
